column5: Anyone hear have any info on head lake near Norland. I'm planning to do some Walleye fishing there this year. Just looking for some tips. We've purchase a cottage near there and would like to narrow things down a bit, with the price of gas thing, should I say anything more. Thanks guys.
The lakes not that big,you wont burn that much fuel out there.LOL  JUST WATCH OUT FOR THE SHOALS AND ROCKS.
Haven't been on the lake for a few years but the launch was actually the public beach.
Yep,it was a beach before.Now it,s the launch.LOL
FF, check your PMs and get back to me.
Hey whats with the pm.......................LOL  Make sure you stop by and pick me up too.

Brian,  I won't be fishing Head lake for a while.  It's Dalrymple this weekend and then lake X (North of Sudbury) next weekend for 5 days with the old man. If you want to have a mini G2G at Head lake later in the summer, we could do that. I know there are other OFNers in the area...
follow the river at the north east end but watch for rocks
Thank you boys. You guys helped me out  . We'll have to get together one day up there and do some fishin and have a cold one, chew the fat. Thanks The Farmer
